  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering penalties can include significant fines and imprisonment. Specific penalties depend on the circumstances, but generally involve:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Potential prison sentences of up to 20 years\n- Fines up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n- Criminal record\n\n2. Factors Influencing Severity:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Involvement in organized crime\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific federal statutes violated\n\nThe primary federal statute covering money laundering is 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956, which details various prohibited financial transactions and associated penalties.",
